There must be a reason. He is on again at 2! He is full of himself. Often wrong but never in doubt.
If there is no disclosure and accountability - viewers are being taken advantage of in the belief that a strategy provides superior returns.

The easiest response is to say critics (like me) are grand standing etc. (which is silly) There is only one reason why its not being done on recommendations (e.g., unusual call activity) - it is not profitable.

Biz media outlets should assign an intern to plug in every investment idea (and their outcomes) and provide that transparency for those traders/investors that request it. If not, its like throwing crap on a wall - seeing what will stick. And that's not an investment strategy.
I have contempt for the media's "carpet sweepers" who fail to be accountable for their investment boners. Case in point: new 52 week low for $KO cnbc.com/video/2018/03/08/fa…
